After hearing about this burger drive-thru joint, from one of my favorite YouTube podcast, Holden Hardman, I had to stop by and try this. I love supporting local businesses when I have the opportunity. But even more when there is amazing value. I had the double patty bacon cheeseburger, large fries and a soda. My gal had the veggie with cheese, large fries and a soda. If If I remember correct it was under $13. It was also the best hamburger I've had that wasn't made at home. Yes it's greasy, as one should expect from a great burger at a drive-thru joint. They very wisely serve it in a suitable wrapper that stands up well. The fries, my wife and I both agree, we're right out of the fryer and good quality. Drive through -  park and eat:  no indoor/outdoor seating. The worst part of this, is the temptation to go back through the line and get another burger! I've been here half a dozen times now - and it's always consistently great. Review updated 17JUN2020.
